                "title": "The weighted doppler transform",
                "year": 2009,
                "venue": "",
                "citation_count": 36,
                "reference_count": 21,
                "abstract": "We consider the tomography problem of recovering a covector field on a simple Riemannian manifold based on its weighted Doppler transformation over a family of curves $\\Gamma$. This is a generalization of the attenuated Doppler transform. Uniqueness is proven for a generic set of weights and families of curves under a condition on the weight function. This condition is satisfied in particular if the weight function is never zero, and its derivatives along the curves in $\\Gamma$ are never zero.",
